OL,3,CAssisted dying bill expected to fail
OL,4,Cin House of Lords today
OL,6,FGood Morning Britain's James Gooderson
OL,7,Freports on a highly controversial bill
OL,8,Fthat has divided MPs, the government
OL,9,Fand the public over the past 18 months
OL,10,Fthat it has been going through
OL,11,FParliament
OL,13,FA bill to legalise assisted dying for
OL,14,Fterminally ill people in England and
OL,15,FWales will formally fail on Friday
OL,16,Fafter running out of time to become
OL,17,Flaw.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777065070
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill expected to fail
OL,4,Cin House of Lords today
OL,6,FThe Terminally Ill Adults (End of
OL,7,FLife) Bill would allow adults with
OL,8,Ffewer than six months to live to apply
OL,9,Ffor assisted death, subject to the
OL,10,Fapproval of two doctors and an expert
OL,11,Fpanel.
OL,13,FThe proposed law has been making its
OL,14,Fway through Parliament for 17 months,
OL,15,Fbut stalled in the House of Lords,
OL,16,Fwith more than 1,200 amendments
OL,17,Fproposed by peers - thought to be a
OL,18,Frecord-breaking amount.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777065070
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill expected to fail
OL,4,Cin House of Lords today
OL,6,FIt is understood the final debate on
OL,7,FFriday is likely to focus on the
OL,8,Fprocess and how the bill has run out
OL,9,Fof time, rather than a continued
OL,10,Fdiscussion on its contents.
OL,12,FMP Kim Leadbeater, who introduced the
OL,13,Fbill to the Commons in late 2024, has
OL,14,Fvowed to enter a ballot to bring it
OL,15,Fback in the next parliamentary session.
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777065070
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill expected to fail
OL,4,Cin House of Lords today
OL,6,FOn the eve of the bill falling,
OL,7,FLeadbeater insisted she will "keep
OL,8,Fpushing for a safer, more
OL,9,Fcompassionate law until Parliament
OL,10,Freaches a final decision".
OL,12,FOf the amendments added to the bill,
OL,13,Fmore than 800 have been tabled or
OL,14,Fsponsored by just seven peers.
OL,16,FThese peers include professor of
OL,17,Fpalliative care Baroness Finlay of
OL,18,FLlandaff and former Paralympian
OL,19,FBaroness Grey-Thompson, who both put
OL,20,Fforward more than 100 each.
OL,26,@oD@^OUrD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777065070
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill expected to fail
OL,4,Cin House of Lords today
OL,6,FA letter to MPs signed by almost 200
OL,7,Fpeers said the bill was set to fall
OL,8,Fdue to "deliberate delaying tactics
OL,9,Fpursued by a minority of peers opposed
OL,10,Fto its passage".
OL,12,F"We regret that this failure will
OL,13,Fdisappoint the overwhelming majority
OL,14,Fof people in this country who support
OL,15,Fa change to the law and were looking
OL,16,Fto Parliament to enact it," the letter
OL,17,Fsaid.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777065070
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill expected to fail
OL,4,Cin House of Lords today
OL,6,F"It is now for the elected chamber to
OL,7,Fdecide what should happen next. We
OL,8,Fbelieve Parliament must come to a
OL,9,Fdecision on choice at the end of life
OL,10,Fas soon as possible," it added.
OL,12,FBaroness Grey-Thompson has denied
OL,13,Fdeliberately blocking the proposed
OL,14,Flaw, calling it a "poorly drafted bill
OL,15,Fwith large gaps" and sharing her
OL,16,Fconcerns about safety and the possible
OL,17,Fcoercion of vulnerable people.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777065070
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill expected to fail
OL,4,Cin House of Lords today
OL,6,FOthers opposed to the bill have
OL,7,Fbranded it "unsafe and unworkable" and
OL,8,F"bad law", citing worries around the
OL,9,Flack of safeguards for those with
OL,10,Fdisabilities.
OL,12,F"The House of Lords have done a
OL,13,Fremarkable job in highlighting the
OL,14,Ffatal flaws in this dangerous and ill-
OL,15,Fconceived bill," said Gordon
OL,16,FMacdonald, CEO of campaign group Care
OL,17,FNot Killing.
OL,26,@oD@LOUoD@bO]pD@AOUpD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
