OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777065070
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill expected to fail
OL,4,Cin House of Lords today
OL,6,FDame Esther Rantzen, a leading voice
OL,7,Fin the campaign to legalise assisted
OL,8,Fdying, accused peers opposed to the
OL,9,Fbill of "condemning generations of
OL,10,Fterminally ill patients to die in
OL,11,Fagony".
OL,13,FRantzen, who was diagnosed with lung
OL,14,Fcancer in 2023 and is terminally ill,
OL,15,Fsaid she was "bitterly disappointed"
OL,16,Fthat some peers had "conspired to
OL,17,Fsabotage our democracy".
OL,19,FCampaign groups in favour of assisted
OL,20,Fdying are urging MPs to bring the bill
OL,21,Fback in the next parliamentary session.
OL,26,@qD@IOUsD@FO]wD@NOUwD@dO]yD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777065070
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill expected to fail
OL,4,Cin House of Lords today
OL,6,F"Dying people want choice and
OL,7,Fcompassion at the end of their lives,"
OL,8,Fsaid Andrew Copson, CEO of charity
OL,9,FHumanists UK.
OL,11,F"The status quo leaves people dying in
OL,12,Fpain with three awful options: fly to
OL,13,FSwitzerland, refuse food and
OL,14,Ftreatment, or suffer. Those options
OL,15,Fare unacceptable."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777065070
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill expected to fail
OL,4,Cin House of Lords today
OL,6,FThe next parliamentary session begins
OL,7,Fafter the King's Speech on May 13, and
OL,8,Fthe government will set out its
OL,9,Flegislative agenda for the coming
OL,10,Fyear, allowing MPs to propose a new
OL,11,Fset of private members' bills (PMBs).
OL,13,FA ballot will then be held to decide
OL,14,Fwhose PMBs are debated first.
OL,16,FMeanwhile, charities working in
OL,17,Fpalliative and end-of-life care have
OL,18,Ftold the health secretary - who voted
OL,19,Fagainst the bill in the Commons - to
OL,20,Fnot let the momentum sparked by
OL,21,Fconversations about death be "wasted".
OL,26,@}D@^OU}D@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
